## Workflow
- Use `/spec` to plan a non-trivial change (3+ files) — produces an approvable plan, then stops
- Use `/craft` to build an approved plan — executes, reviews with `/vet` + `/exercise`, stops for ship
- Use `/vet` for a standalone pre-merge code review (clean-context reviewer)
- Use `/git-save` when ready to commit
- Use `/slop-scan` to detect tech debt

## What NOT to do
- Don't add features beyond what was asked
- Don't refactor code you didn't change
- Don't add comments to self-explanatory code
- Don't commit .env files or secrets
